Zhirinovsky demands that references to fraternal peoples be removed from the Russian anthem.
LDPR leader, Vladimir Zhirinovsky, believes that references to the union of fraternal peoples should be removed from the national anthem.
He spoke about this during a session of the State Duma, reports the Russian News Service.
